title.narrative: Coefficient of internal efficiency

description.narrative: The coefficient of internal efficiency represents the ideal number of pupil-years required, i.e. without repetition and / or dropout, to produce a number of graduates from a given school-cohort for a cycle or level of education. This is expressed as a percentage of the actual number of pupil-years spent to produce the same number of graduates. As such, this indicator conveys the extent to which an education system manages to minimise wastage of student time in helping them pass through their educational itinerary. It is, therefore, an indicator of educational system efficiency.
